ENV VARIABLES TO ADD in server/.env:
  GEMINI_API_KEY_1=your_main_key
  GEMINI_API_KEY_2=your_jio_key_1
  GEMINI_API_KEY_3=your_jio_key_2
  GEMINI_API_KEY_4=your_student_key
  REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
  GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token
  DOCKER_ENABLED=true
  DOCKER_TIMEOUT=60000

FILES TO CREATE:
  ❌ server/services/gemini.service.js
     → Round robin across 4 API keys
     → Tracks current key index
     → Rotates on each request
     → Falls back if one key fails

  ❌ server/services/github.service.js
     → Takes GitHub repo URL
     → Uses @octokit/rest to fetch file tree
     → Downloads README.md, package.json
     → Downloads all .js .jsx .ts .tsx files
     → Returns combined code string

  ❌ server/services/docker.service.js
     → Creates isolated container (node:18-alpine)
     → Copies student code inside
     → Runs: npm install && npm test
     → Captures stdout and stderr
     → Destroys container after 60 seconds
     → Returns test results

  ❌ server/services/evaluation.service.js
     → Orchestrates the full pipeline:
       1. Get submission from DB
       2. Fetch code (GitHub API or ZIP extract)
       3. Run in Docker container
       4. Send code + test results to Gemini
       5. Parse Gemini JSON response
       6. Save Score to DB
       7. Update submission status to completed

  ❌ server/workers/evaluation.worker.js
     → Bull queue worker
     → Listens for new evaluation jobs
     → Calls evaluation.service.js
     → Handles errors and retries
     → Updates submission status on failure

  ❌ server/queues/evaluation.queue.js
     → Bull queue setup
     → Redis connection
     → Queue configuration (retries, timeout)

FLOW:
  createSubmission() → adds job to Bull queue
  worker picks job → fetches code → runs Docker
  → Gemini evaluates → Score saved → status: completed

